{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:06:37.213390+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have all the information needed. Here is a summary of the repository.\n\n---\n\n## Runtime Profiles\n\nThe template defines **five runtime profiles**, documented in the `README.md`:\n\n| Profile | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| **local** | Configures an environment that can be developed even without network connectivity (fully offline-capable). |\n| **local-dev** | Allows a developer’s local machine to connect to the **DEV** environment. |\n| **dev** | Used for deploying **Development** environments. |\n| **staging** | Used for deploying **Staging** environments. |\n| **live** | Used for deploying **Live/Production** environments. |\n\n> **Note from `CONTRIBUTING.md`** – until the profile cleanup is complete, contributors should **ignore the `local-dev`, `staging`, and `live` profile descriptions** and reason only about local execution.\n\n---\n\n## Test Tasks & Tags\n\nThe build (`build.gradle`) defines five JUnit Platform‑based test suites:\n\n| Task | Tag filter | Purpose |\n|------|------------|---------|\n| **`test`** (default) | Excludes `develop`, `restdocs` | A collection of tests that should run on CI. |\n| **`unitTest`** | Excludes `develop`, `context`, `restdocs` | Fast, dependency‑free tests that verify a single feature. |\n| **`contextTest`** | Includes `context` | Integration tests that require a Spring ApplicationContext. |\n| **`restDocsTest`** | Includes `restdocs` | Tests that produce AsciiDoc snippets via Spring REST Docs. |\n| **`developTest`** | Includes `develop` | Tests that should **not** run on CI (useful for work‑in‑progress tests). |\n\n---\n\n## Recommended Developer Setup for Linting & Running Tests\n\n### 1. Git Hook – Linting on Every Commit\nA pre‑commit hook is provided at `.githooks/pre-commit`. It runs `./gradlew checkFormat` before each commit. To enable it:\n\n```bash\ngit config core.hookspath .githooks\n```\n\n### 2. IntelliJ IDEA – Running Tests\nTo make test execution work seamlessly out of the box without Gradle re‑wrapping:\n\n```\nBuild, Execution, Deployment → Build Tools → Gradle → Run tests using → IntelliJ IDEA\n```\n\n### 3. Code Formatting (Linting)\n- The project uses **Spring Java Format** (`io.spring.javaformat`) declared in `lint.gradle` – every subproject applies both the `java` plugin and the formatting plugin.\n- The `.springjavaformatconfig` file sets `indentation-style=spaces`.\n- To apply the same formatting rules inside IntelliJ IDEA, install the [Spring Java Format plugin](https://github.com/spring-io/spring-javaformat#intellij-idea).\n\n### 4. Java & Build Tooling\n- **Java version**: 25 (set in `gradle.properties` as `javaVersion=25`).\n- **Build system**: Gradle (Wrapper scripts `gradlew` / `gradlew.bat` provided).\n- **Dependency management**: All dependency versions are centralized in `gradle.properties`.\n\n### Summary of Key Gradle Commands\n\n| Action | Command |\n|--------|---------|\n| Run default tests (CI suite) | `./gradlew test` |\n| Run unit tests only | `./gradlew unitTest` |\n| Run context (integration) tests | `./gradlew contextTest` |\n| Run REST Docs tests | `./gradlew restDocsTest` |\n| Run develop‑only tests | `./gradlew developTest` |\n| Check formatting | `./gradlew checkFormat` |\n| Apply formatting | `./gradlew format` |", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1306, "prompt_tokens": 8762, "total_tokens": 10068, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 503, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 8576}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 8576, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 186}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "d4e12381-1057-4256-894a-256a